      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef optimize_order_flow(orders):\n    \"\"\"Sorts orders by price (descending) then by timestamp (ascending).\"\"\"\n    return sorted(orders, key=lambda x: (-x['price'], x['timestamp']))\n```\nThis function uses a lambda key to sort first by the negative price (achieving descending order) and then by the timestamp (ascending). It is concise and directly addresses the dual sorting requirement for your HFT engine. This implementation is robust enough to pass standard validation checks.",
